__commit_message__ = 'feat(diff): connection retry, error surfacing, and design doc\n\nfigmaclaw diff was silently dropping files when large file-tree downloads\nfailed mid-stream with httpx.RemoteProtocolError. The error was caught by\nasyncio.gather(return_exceptions=True) and then filtered out of results,\nso the user saw a clean output that was actually missing data.\n\nFixes:\n- figma_client._get / _get_url now retry on RemoteProtocolError, ReadError,\n  ReadTimeout, and ConnectError with the same exponential backoff used for\n  5xx. Large get_file_full responses (50+ MB for Mobile App) are prone to\n  stream truncation and need this.\n- diff._run now surfaces failed files to stderr instead of silently dropping\n  them, and also logs "N versions but no structural frame changes" for\n  active files that had edits-only activity.\n- Tests: test_retries_on_connection_drop, test_retries_on_read_timeout.\n\nAlso adds docs/design-weekly-report.md — the design doc for the weekly\ndesign report work, capturing the goal, approach, what\'s done, interim\nresults, open questions, and the full TODO list (P0–P3).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>'
